This paper deals with the problem of multi-robot multi-target tracking, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of multiple sub-fields in computer science. The use of motion primitives and algorithms for maximizing the number of targets tracked or the total quality of tracking suggests that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) or cs.RO (Robotics). The focus on limited communication and the development of distributed algorithms suggests that cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely sub-category. The use of algorithms for finding approximations to optimal solutions suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible sub-categories.
